<item>
            <title>[HIVE-6558] HiveServer2 Plain SASL authentication broken after hadoop 2.3 upgrade</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-6558</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Java only includes Plain SASL client and not server. Hence HiveServer2 includes a Plain SASL server implementation. Now Hadoop has its own Plain SASL server &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-9020&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;HADOOP-9020&lt;/a&gt; which is part of Hadoop 2.3 &lt;a href=&quot;http://hadoop.apache.org/docs/r2.3.0/hadoop-project-dist/hadoop-common/releasenotes.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;release&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
The two servers use different Sasl callbacks and the servers are registered in java.security.Provider via static code. As a result the HiveServer2 instance could be using Hadoop&apos;s Plain SASL server which breaks the authentication.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
